            "id": "b1eef76ad4f34c9b9b962",
            "questionText": "A cyclist pedals up a hill with a constant speed. The hill has a height of $!$50\\text{ m}$!$ and the cyclist and bicycle have a combined weight of $!$700\\text{ N}$!$. The cyclist's power output is $!$100\\text{ W}$!$ and they take $!$60\\text{ s}$!$ to reach the top. The cyclist's body consumes $!$5000\\text{ J}$!$ of energy during that time. Determine the efficiency of the cyclist's energy conversion during the ascent.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "61ed7296c5cb4663be72b",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the relation between power, time, and work done. Identify the formula that correctly relates these quantities.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "67784893-a7f7-4ebc-ac63-a3f494a49df0",
                        "2691d473-fa9f-48af-866f-fcf735cf65ac"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$W = P \\times t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$W = \\frac{P}{t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$W = P + t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "3d1e86620b5b47f681215",
                    "stepText": "Now, use the given power output and time to calculate the mechanical work done during the ascent.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "6000"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "J",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "67784893-a7f7-4ebc-ac63-a3f494a49df0",
                        "2691d473-fa9f-48af-866f-fcf735cf65ac"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "eee9f064073b4a22b20f6",
                    "stepText": "Next, to find the efficiency, identify the correct concept that expresses efficiency as a ratio. Which of the following formulas represents efficiency?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
