        {
            "id": "f8fde2dc66fa4b8f845de",
            "questionText": "A delivery company's electric van accelerates from rest to a speed of $!$20 \\text{ m/s}$!$ on a horizontal road. During this acceleration, the motor does $!$500,000 \\text{ J}$!$ of work. After this, the van travels up a hill, gaining $!$10\\text{ m}$!$ in vertical height. If the van's mass is $!$1500\\text{ kg}$!$, what is the total change in the van's mechanical energy from the start of the acceleration to reaching the height of $!$10\\text{ m}$!$ on the hill?",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "b36d4d4eb4e44ddeac1ae",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying which formula correctly represents the kinetic energy of an object. Please select the correct formula from the options provided.",
